headline.main: TURKS CONFIDENT ON NEUTRAL STAND; Government Circles Found Believing That Nation Will Traverse Crisis Safely

lead_paragraph: ANKARA, Turkey, Sept. 27 -- Turkish Government circles radiated confidence tonight that Turkey would emerge from the coming critical week and the entire Autumn with existing alliances and ententes intact, preserving the republic's armed neutrality in the face of crises affecting Turkey, Southeastern Europe and the whole Middle East.
abstract: Turks confident of preserving neutrality; Brit reassured by significant contract to Brit firm for bldg dock facilities at Mersina and Alexandretta ports; von Papen reptd due in Ankara; Knatchbull-Hugessen conf with Saracoglu
